  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The hypothesis is that patients with poorly controlled diabetes would have greater
      improvement in their blood sugar control when managed by a clinical pharmacist than when
      managed with usual medical care. Patients with poor control are randomized to pharmacist
      management or to usual medical care for one year.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
